## Gemini CLI command cheatsheet

**Inside a Gemini session:**

| Command | What it does |
|---|---|
| `/quit` or Ctrl-D | Exit the session |
| `/help` | Show slash commands |
| `/clear` | Clear screen (session context preserved) |
| `/compress` | Compress conversation history when context gets heavy |
| `@path/to/file` | Inject a file's content into your next message |
| Shift-Tab | Accept a pending edit |
| Esc | Reject a pending edit / cancel |

**Launching Gemini (from shell):**

| Flag | When to use |
|---|---|
| `gemini` | Normal interactive launch |
| `gemini "your prompt"` | Launch with an initial prompt |
| `gemini -r latest` | Resume the most recent session |
| `gemini --list-sessions` | List resumable sessions, then exit |
| `gemini -p "prompt"` | Headless one-shot (no interactive mode) |
| `gemini --include-directories ~/other/path` | Add another folder to workspace |
| `gemini --approval-mode default` | Prompt before edits (keep this as default) |
| `gemini --approval-mode plan` | Plan-first mode for complex tasks |

**Don't use** `--yolo` or `--approval-mode yolo` on operational work. Your append-only and review-before-send discipline depends on seeing each change.

