## Injecting file content with @

The `@` syntax is useful when you want Gemini to focus on a specific file without scanning the tree:

```
Summarize @current/cyber-events/2026-04-21-akamai-advisory/cyber-event-record.md
in 3 sentences.
```

```
Compare @inbox/vendor-claim.extracted.md against
@context/playbooks.yaml — which playbook applies?
```

Works across the workspace. Tab-completes the path.

