## Failure modes and fixes

| Symptom | Likely cause | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| Gemini rewrites a record instead of appending | Drift from GEMINI.md rule | Revert via OneDrive version history. Add a specific sentence to GEMINI.md naming the drift you saw. |
| Gemini stops referencing context/ mid-session | Context amnesia | `Re-read context/communication-style.yaml before the next draft.` |
| File-read error in OneDrive folder | Files On-Demand un-downloaded it | In Finder, select folder → right-click → Always Keep on This Device. |
| Gemini proposes a file path that doesn't exist | Path hallucination | Ask it to `ls` the parent folder first, then correct. |
| Non-text file extraction is garbled | .docx/.pdf limits | Open in native app, copy text, paste into the `.extracted.md` yourself. |
| Gemini classifies a case wrong (e.g., third-party as incident) | Route confusion | Correct explicitly, then: `Update GEMINI.md with a sentence naming the signal that distinguishes these.` |
| Terminal feels slow on large workspace | Archive scanning on every read | Add a `.geminiignore` file at root with `archive/` and `.obsidian/` listed. |
| VS Code doesn't show Gemini's edits | Editor tab cached | Click the tab, or Cmd-Shift-P → "Revert File". |

