## What stays in Terminal, what stays in VS Code

**Terminal only:**
- Talking to Gemini
- Launching sessions, resuming, switching modes
- Asking Gemini to create, move, or edit files

**VS Code only:**
- Hand-editing YAML context files
- Reading drafts, records, templates
- Browsing the tree via Explorer sidebar
- Searching across files (Cmd-Shift-F)
- Version-control-style review of Gemini's pending edits (if you use the Git integration and commit snapshots)

**Either:**
- Opening a file for reference
- Quick peek at session log

